Adaro Energy, Harum, Medco, Timah: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-04-13T02:06:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/adaro-energy-harum-medco-timah-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  slid 0.7 percent to 3,719.23.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures declined 3.3 percent to
$106.25 a barrel in  New York  yesterday, capping the biggest two-
day drop in almost 11 months. Oil was at $105.95 a barrel in
after-hours trading as of 8:08 a.m. Jakarta time.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),  Indonesia ’s
biggest listed oil company, fell 1.8 percent to 2,800 rupiah and
PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ), the second largest, retreated
2.3 percent to 126 rupiah.  Metal producers: Nickel for three month delivery dropped
3.6 percent to $26,700 a metric ton in  London  yesterday, the
most since March 15. Tin lost 2.3 percent to $32,550 a ton.  PT International Nickel Indonesia (INCO IJ), the nation’s
biggest producer of the metal, retreated 0.5 percent to 4,875
rupiah and PT Timah (TINS IJ), Indonesia’s largest tin producer,
fell 2.6 percent to 2,825 rupiah.  PT Bank Internasional Indonesia (BNII IJ): Malayan Banking
Bhd.,  Malaysia ’s biggest lender by assets, plans to ask
Indonesia’s regulator for an extension to sell down its stakes
in Bank Internasional Indonesia, Chief Executive Officer Abdul
Wahid Omar said in an interview in  Kuala Lumpur . Maybank has
until June to sell down its stake in the bank from 97 percent
currently to 80 percent, Abdul Wahid said. Bank Internasional
declined 1.6 percent to 610 rupiah.  PT Adaro Energy (ADRO IJ): Indonesia’s second-largest coal
producer was cut to “underperform” from “neutral” at Credit
Suisse Group AG, which cited the potential for earnings
downgrades. The brokerage reduced its share-price forecast to
2,050 rupiah from 2,600 rupiah, according to a report by Fonny
Surya. Adaro fell 1.1 percent to 2,275 rupiah.  PT Harum Energy (HRUM IJ): The Indonesian coal producer was
rated “neutral” in new coverage at Credit Suisse Group AG. The
brokerage has a share-price forecast of 9,600 rupiah, according
to a report by Fonny Surya. Harum declined 1.6 percent to 9,100
rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
